Two trucks collided head-on in an accident on the N1 between Beaufort West and Three Sisters in the early hours on Wednesday. Four people have been reported dead, said Ntomboxolo Makoba-Somdaka, spokesperson for Western Cape minister of transport and public works, Bonginkosi Madikizela. Both vehicles caught fire. The road was temporarily closed. Motorists were advised to use the alternative route Aberdeen-Graaff Reinet-Murraysburg and back onto the N1. One lane has since been reopened. TimesLIVE